2500|$|Since {{commercial}} arbitration {{is based upon}} either contract law or the law of treaties, the agreement between the parties to submit their dispute to arbitration is a legally <b>binding</b> <b>contract.</b> All arbitral decisions {{are considered to be}} [...] "final and binding." [...] This does not, however, void the requirements of law. Any dispute not excluded from arbitration by virtue of law (for example, criminal proceedings) may be submitted to arbitration.|$|E
